In PHP, the `strpos()` function is used to find the position of the first occurrence of a substring within a string. To reverse the functionality of `strpos()`, you can create a custom function that finds the position of the last occurrence of a substring within a string. Here's an example:

```php
function strrpos_reverse($haystack, $needle) {
    $lastPos = -1;
    $offset = 0;

    while (($pos = strpos($haystack, $needle, $offset)) !== false) {
        $lastPos = $pos;
        $offset = $pos + 1;
    }

    return $lastPos;
}

// Usage example
$string = "Hello World! Hello World!";
$substring = "World";

$lastPos = strrpos_reverse($string, $substring);
echo "Last occurrence of '$substring' starts at position $lastPos";
```

