To match and replace text that is not within a link using regex and DOMDocument in PHP, you can follow these steps:

1. Load the HTML content into a DOMDocument object.
2. Use XPath to select all text nodes that are not within an `<a>` tag.
3. Iterate over the selected text nodes and replace the desired text using regex.
4. Save the modified HTML content.

Here's an example code snippet that demonstrates this process:

```php
// HTML content
$html = '<p>This is a sample text. <a href="#">This is a link</a>. This is another sample text.</p>';

// Load HTML into DOMDocument
$dom = new DOMDocument();
$dom->loadHTML($html);

// Create XPath object
$xpath = new DOMXPath($dom);

// Select all text nodes not within an <a> tag
$textNodes = $xpath->query('//text()[not(ancestor::a)]');

// Regex pattern to match the text you want to replace
$pattern = '/sample text/';

// Replacement text
$replacement = 'replacement text';

// Iterate over the selected text nodes and replace the desired text
foreach ($textNodes as $textNode) {
    $text = $textNode->nodeValue;
    $modifiedText = preg_replace($pattern, $replacement, $text);
    $textNode->nodeValue = $modifiedText;
}

// Save the modified HTML content
$modifiedHtml = $dom->saveHTML();

echo $modifiedHtml;
```

In this example, the regex pattern `/sample text/` is used to match the text "sample text" that is not within an `<a>` tag. The replacement text is set to "replacement text". The resulting modified HTML content will have the matched text replaced with the replacement text, but only if it is not within a link.

