This error typically occurs when there is a missing closing brace or parenthesis in your PHP code. To fix this error, you need to carefully check your code and make sure all opening braces and parentheses have a corresponding closing brace or parenthesis.

Here are some common scenarios that can cause this error:

1. Missing closing brace in a control structure (if, for, while, etc.):
```php
if ($condition) {
    // code...
} // Missing closing brace
```
To fix this, add the missing closing brace at the end of the control structure:
```php
if ($condition) {
    // code...
} // Closing brace added
```

2. Missing closing parenthesis in a function call or declaration:
```php
function myFunction($param1, $param2 {
    // code...
} // Missing closing parenthesis
```
To fix this, add the missing closing parenthesis at the end of the function declaration:
```php
function myFunction($param1, $param2) {
    // code...
} // Closing parenthesis added
```

3. Missing closing parenthesis in an array declaration:
```php
$array = array('item1', 'item2';
```
To fix this, add the missing closing parenthesis at the end of the array declaration:
```php
$array = array('item1', 'item2');
```

Make sure to carefully review your code and check for any missing closing braces or parentheses.

