HTML scraping in PHP refers to the process of extracting data from HTML web pages using PHP programming language. It involves parsing the HTML code of a web page and extracting specific elements or data from it.

There are several libraries and tools available in PHP for HTML scraping, such as:

1. DOMDocument: It is a built-in PHP class that provides a convenient way to parse and manipulate HTML documents. It allows you to traverse the HTML structure and extract data using various methods and properties.

Example usage:

```php
$html = file_get_contents('https://example.com');
$dom = new DOMDocument();
$dom->loadHTML($html);

// Extract specific elements
$titles = $dom->getElementsByTagName('title');
foreach ($titles as $title) {
    echo $title->nodeValue;
}

$links = $dom->getElementsByTagName('a');
foreach ($links as $link) {
    echo $link->getAttribute('href');
}
```

2. Simple HTML DOM: It is a PHP library that provides an easy way to manipulate HTML elements using a jQuery-like syntax. It allows you to find elements by CSS selectors and extract data from them.

Example usage:

```php
include 'simple_html_dom.php';

$html = file_get_html('https://example.com');

// Extract specific elements
$titles = $html->find('title');
foreach ($titles as $title) {
    echo $title->plaintext;
}

$links = $html->find('a');
foreach ($links as $link) {
    echo $link->href;
}
```

3. Guzzle: It is a popular PHP HTTP client library that can be used for making HTTP requests and retrieving HTML content from web pages. It provides a simple and flexible API for handling HTTP requests and responses.

Example usage:

```php
require 'vendor/autoload.php';

use GuzzleHttp\Client;

$client = new Client();
$response = $client->request('GET', 'https://example.com');
$html = $response->getBody()->getContents();

// Extract specific elements
$titles = [];
$dom = new DOMDocument();
$dom->loadHTML($html);
$titles = $dom->getElementsByTagName('title');
foreach ($titles as $title) {
    echo $title->nodeValue;
}

$links = [];
$dom = new DOMDocument();
$dom->loadHTML($html);
$links = $dom->getElementsByTagName('a');
foreach ($links as $link) {
    echo $link->getAttribute('href');
}
```

These are just a few examples of how you can perform HTML scraping in PHP. Depending on your specific requirements, you may need to use additional libraries or techniques to handle more complex scenarios.

