```

In this example, we have an XML string with three nodes (`node1`, `node2`, and `node3`). We want to insert a new node (`newNode`) at position 1, which means it will be inserted after `node1` and before `node2`.

First, we load the XML string using `simplexml_load_string()`. Then, we create a new node using the `addChild()` method and assign it to the `$newNode` variable.

Next, we get the desired position where we want to insert the new node. In this case, we set it to 1.

To insert the new node at the desired position, we convert the SimpleXML object to an array using `json_decode(json_encode($simplexml), true)`. Then, we use the `array_splice()` function to insert the new node at the specified position.

