2. JavaScript (script.js):
```javascript
document.getElementById('csvFile').addEventListener('change', handleFileSelect, false);

function handleFileSelect(event) {
    const file = event.target.files[0];
    const reader = new FileReader();

    reader.onload = function (e) {
        const contents = e.target.result;
        const rows = contents.split('\n');

        let tableHtml = '<table>';

        rows.forEach(function (row, index) {
            const columns = row.split(',');

            if (index === 0) {
                tableHtml += '<thead><tr>';
                columns.forEach(function (column) {
                    tableHtml += '<th>' + column + '</th>';
                });
                tableHtml += '</tr></thead><tbody>';
            } else {
                tableHtml += '<tr>';
                columns.forEach(function (column) {
                    tableHtml += '<td>' + column + '</td>';
                });
                tableHtml += '</tr>';
            }
        });

        tableHtml += '</tbody></table>';

        document.getElementById('tableContainer').innerHTML = tableHtml;
    };

    reader.readAsText(file);
}
```

In this example, we have an HTML input element of type "file" to allow the user to select a CSV file. When the file is selected, the `handleFileSelect` function is triggered.

Inside the `handleFileSelect` function, we use the FileReader API to read the contents of the selected file. We split the contents by newline character to get an array of rows. Then, we iterate over each row and split it by comma to get an array of columns.

We dynamically generate the HTML table by concatenating the table structure and the values from the CSV file. The first row is treated as the table header, and the remaining rows are treated as table data.

Finally, we set the generated HTML table as the innerHTML of the `tableContainer` div element to display it on the web page.

Note: This example assumes that the CSV file has a header row. If your CSV file doesn't have a header row, you can modify the code accordingly.

