    $files = scandir($dir);
    foreach ($files as $file) {
        if ($file === '.' || $file === '..') {
            continue;
        }

        $path = $dir . '/' . $file;
        if (is_dir($path)) {
            removeDirectory($path);
        } else {
            unlink($path);
        }
    }

    rmdir($dir);
}
```

You can use this function to remove a directory and all its contents recursively. It first checks if the given path is a directory. If not, it returns. Otherwise, it scans the directory and iterates over each file and subdirectory. If it encounters a subdirectory, it calls the `removeDirectory` function recursively. If it encounters a file, it deletes it using the `unlink` function. Finally, it removes the empty directory using the `rmdir` function.

