$returnValue = 0;
exec($command, $output, $returnValue);

if ($returnValue !== 0) {
    echo "SCP command failed: " . implode("\n", $output);
} else {
    echo "File copied successfully!";
}
```

By examining the output and error messages, you should be able to identify the specific issue preventing the file from being copied to the remote server.

