    public function testMagicGet() {
        $mock = $this->getMockBuilder(MyClass::class)
            ->setMethods(['__get'])
            ->getMock();

        $mock->expects($this->once())
            ->method('__get')
            ->with('property_name')
            ->willReturn('property_value');

        $this->assertEquals('property_value', $mock->property_name);
    }
}
```

In the above example, we are mocking the `__get()` magic method of the `MyClass` class. We specify the method to be mocked using `setMethods(['__get'])` and then define the expectations for the method using `expects($this->once())->method('__get')`. We also provide the required argument for the `__get()` method using `->with('property_name')`.

By providing the required argument for the `__get()` method, you can avoid the error "__get() must take exactly 1 argument ..." in PHPUnit.

