In Laravel, you can put and handle enums in different ways depending on your preference and the specific use case. Here are a few common approaches:

1. Define enums as classes: Create a separate directory within your app directory, such as `app/Enums`, and define each enum as a class within this directory. Each enum class can have constants representing the possible values. For example:

```php
namespace App\Enums;

