In this example, replace `/path/to/your/script.sh` with the actual path to your shell script. The `exec()` function takes the shell script path as the first argument and an optional array to store the output lines as the second argument. The third argument is used to capture the return value of the shell script.

You can also use the backtick operator to execute the shell script:

```php
<?php
$scriptPath = '/path/to/your/script.sh';

