?>
```

In this example, the backtick operator is used to execute the shell script and capture its output directly into the `$output` variable. The output can then be displayed using the `echo` statement.

Note: Executing shell scripts from a PHP script can be a security risk if not handled properly. Make sure to validate and sanitize any user input before passing it to the shell script to prevent command injection attacks.

