Yes, it is possible to change a user's profile image using the Facebook Graph API with PHP. 

To change a user's profile image, you need to have the `publish_actions` permission from the user. Here are the steps to change a user's profile image:

1. Get the user's access token with the `publish_actions` permission.
2. Upload the new profile image to Facebook using the `/me/photos` endpoint. This will return the ID of the uploaded photo.
3. Set the uploaded photo as the user's profile picture using the `/me/picture` endpoint.

Here is an example code snippet to change a user's profile image using the Facebook Graph API with PHP:

```php
<?php
// Step 1: Get the user's access token with the publish_actions permission
$access_token = 'USER_ACCESS_TOKEN';

// Step 2: Upload the new profile image to Facebook
$photo_url = 'PATH_TO_NEW_PROFILE_IMAGE';
$caption = 'New Profile Image';

$response = file_get_contents(
  'https://graph.facebook.com/v12.0/me/photos?access_token=' . $access_token,
  false,
  stream_context_create([
    'http' => [
      'method' => 'POST',
      'header' => 'Content-Type: multipart/form-data',
      'content' => http_build_query([
        'caption' => $caption,
        'source' => new CURLFile($photo_url),
      ]),
    ],
  ])
);

$photo_id = json_decode($response)->id;

// Step 3: Set the uploaded photo as the user's profile picture
$response = file_get_contents(
  'https://graph.facebook.com/v12.0/me/picture?access_token=' . $access_token,
  false,
  stream_context_create([
    'http' => [
      'method' => 'POST',
      'header' => 'Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded',
      'content' => http_build_query([
        'picture' => $photo_id,
      ]),
    ],
  ])
);

echo 'Profile image changed successfully!';
?>
```

Make sure to replace `USER_ACCESS_TOKEN` with the actual user access token and `PATH_TO_NEW_PROFILE_IMAGE` with the path to the new profile image on your server.

