```php
use Illuminate\Support\Facades\Storage;

public function downloadFile($filename)
{
    $path = storage_path('app/public/' . $filename);

    if (Storage::exists($path)) {
        return response()->download($path)->deleteFileAfterSend(true);
    }

    abort(404);
}
```

In this example, we first check if the file exists in the storage directory using the `Storage::exists()` method. If the file exists, we return a response with the `download()` method, which will download the file to the user's browser. We then chain the `deleteFileAfterSend(true)` method to delete the file after it has been sent to the user.

